  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/3253",
  "title": "feat(panel): add Panel widget",
  "body": "The panel widget adds a way to wrap other widgets to add templates (headers, footers) and utility features (collapsing and hiding the widget).\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\n\r\nUsing headers and footers wrapping a widget is a common need to give more context to the user when interacting with the widget.\r\n\r\nReact InstantSearch provides a `Panel` widget to wrap any other InstantSearch component:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n<Panel header=\"All brands\">\r\n  <RefinementList attributes=\"brands\" />\r\n</Panel>\r\n```\r\n\r\nUp until InstantSearch.js 2, widgets had `header` and `footer` templates, in addition to [`autoHideContainer`](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets-common-api.html#autohidecontainer) and [`collapsible`](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets-common-api.html#collapsible) options. The panel widget solves these needs, deferring the responsability from the widget itself to the panel widget.\r\n\r\n## Usage\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst refinementListWithPanel = panel({\r\n  templates: {\r\n    header: 'Header',\r\n    footer: 'Footer',\r\n    // or with functions\r\n    header: ({ results }) => `Header | ${results.nbHits} results`,\r\n  },\r\n  hidden: ({ results }) => results.nbHits === 0,\r\n})(refinementList);\r\n\r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n  refinementListWithPanel({\r\n    attribute: 'brands',\r\n  })\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe `hidden` property drives the `noRefinement` CSS class.\r\n\r\n## Specs\r\n\r\nhttps://instantsearch-css.netlify.com/widgets/panel/\r\n\r\n## RFC\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/algolia/instantsearch-rfcs/pull/9\r\n\r\n## Preview\r\n\r\nhttps://deploy-preview-3253--instantsearchjs.netlify.com/stories/?selectedStory=Panel.with%20default",
